mondrian.rolap

Class RolapCacheRegion

  • java.lang.Object
    • mondrian.rolap.RolapCacheRegion

  • public class RolapCacheRegion
extends Object
    A RolapCacheRegion represents a region of multidimensional space in the cache.

    The region is represented in terms of the columns of a given RolapStar, and constraints on those columns.

    Compare with CacheControl.CellRegion: a CellRegion is in terms of Member objects (logical); whereas a RolapCacheRegion is in terms of columns (physical).

      • addPredicate

        public void addPredicate(StarPredicate predicate)
        Adds a predicate which applies to multiple columns.

        The typical example of a multi-column predicate is a member constraint. For example, the constraint "m between 1997.Q3 and 1998.Q2" translates into "year = 1997 and quarter >= Q3 or year = 1998 and quarter <= Q2".

        Parameters:
        predicate - Predicate
